                        <interp inst="t18770917-name-163" type="surname" value="NORTH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770917-name-163" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM NORTH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">re-examination continued</hi>). I did not see Mr. Hands at New<lb></lb>ington Causeway at the time of the bankruptcy and tell him 1 had taken about 500<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. of my best book debts out of the books; I never had 500<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.; I did not tell him that I did not intend to give any account of them, that I had put some goods into the chaff-bin which the ostler had covered over with sacks, and that when they came to my house to search they found nothing but the old van—I did not say I had sent goods away to Royston; I had sent goods belonging to the Thompsons at the time of their failure—I did not say that I thought I should clear about 700<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. by the stock, and 500<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. by the book debts—I did not say I only wanted about 1,000<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., and I should take a public-house.</p>
