                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. METCALFE</hi>. North paid me for the other journeys, but no one paid me the last 25<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—the goods were done up in canvas as they came from the warehouse; they did not appear to have been undone—I took, one load to the Causeway, not latterly, that was about 10th May, 1875.</p>
