                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Detective Officer</hi>). On 2nd May, I went to Tottenham, and saw Walter Thompson on the way to the railway station about 10 o'clock—I told him I was a detective officer, and should have to take him into custody on a charge of conspiracy between him and his' brothers and other persons to. defraud various persons in the City—he asked me for my warrant—I showed him my card as a detective, and explained that I had not a warrant—he asked to be allowed to go home—I told him he could not—I took him to the Moor Lane station where the warrant was read to him—he said at the railway station that he thought a summons might have answered the purpose—I searched and found on him two duplicates for 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. and 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., two deposit notes for 15<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. and 35<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.</p>
