                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City Detective</hi>). On 7th May, I took Alfred Thompson in High Street, Stoke Newington—I told him the charge—he said—"I 'have not the slightest fear of anybody proving anything" against me, I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="187709170140"></xptr>
               <p>have had nothing that I have not paid for"—I took him to Moor Lane station, and the charge was read over to him—I found on him four cheques, three duplicates, the counterfoils of a cheque-book, a post-office book, various letters, and a bunch of keys, which were given to Sergeant Smith.</p>
